This is how to split_words of txt:
  Remember that words is []
  Remember that current is []
  Remember that text_mode is no
  When isstring of txt is yes, then:
    Remember that text_mode is yes
  End when
  Do this txt's length times:
    Remember that i is diff of txt's length and current's length
  End do
  Remember that i is 0
  Do this txt's length times:
    Remember that ch is item i in txt
    Remember that is_sep is no
    When text_mode is yes, then:
      When ch is " ", then:
        Remember that is_sep is yes
      End when
      When ch is ",", then:
        Remember that is_sep is yes
      End when
    But, if not:
      When ch is 32, then:
        Remember that is_sep is yes
      End when
      When ch is 44, then:
        Remember that is_sep is yes
      End when
    End when
    When is_sep is yes, then:
      When current's length is more than 0, then:
        Add words to current
        Remember that current is []
      End when
    But, if not:
      Add current to ch
    End when
    Increase i by 1
  End do
  When current's length is more than 0, then:
    Add words to current
  End when
  The answer is words
